Package hr.fer.zemris.java.tecaj.hw07.shell.commands

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ShellCommand
    ShellCommand represents an executable command in a shell.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractShellCommand
    Implements some default functionality of ShellCommand and implements some additional command which are useful for executing each shell command.
    CatShellCommand
    Cat command opens given file and writes it to console.
    CharsetsShellCommand
    Command charsets takes no arguments and lists names of supported charsets for your Java platform.
    CopyShellCommand
    Copy command copies a file to given path.
    ExitShellCommand
    Exit command sends signal to shell to stop taking commands.
    HelpShellCommand
    Help command provides information on existing shell commands of the environment in which is executed.
    HexdumpShellCommand
    Hexdump produces a hex output of a file.
    LsShellCommand
    Ls command writes a directory listing (not recursive).
    MkdirShellCommand
    The Mkdir command takes a single argument: directory name, and creates the appropriate directory structure.
    SymbolShellCommand
    Symbol command expects 1 or 2 arguments.
    TreeShellCommand
    The tree command expects a single argument: directory name and prints a tree of the directory.
